description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have you ever thought about returning to nursing practice!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Then you&#39;re in the right place!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What is Return to Nursing Practice?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Return to nursing practice (RtNP) gives people who have been previously registered nurses the opportunity to return to the profession by undertaking a return to nursing practice course.  RtNP offers healthcare providers such as Southern Health NHS Foundation Trust the opportunity to work in partnership with the university to support the Return to Nursing Practice course offering clinical placements within our Trust to complete the set clinical hours.   &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In order to be eligible for readmission to the register you must have either:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completed 750 hours of practice in the previous five years, or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completed 450 hours of practice in the previous three years, or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completed the equivalent number of registered practice hours whilst registered with the relevant regulator overseas, or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successfully completed an NMC approved return to nursing practice programme, or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take a &lt;strong&gt;test of competence&lt;/strong&gt; (available from January 2020)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How is the Return to Nursing Practice Funded?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Return to Nursing Practice returners with placements in the South, Health Education England will fund the University fee directly and also provide a £500 stipend, which will be paid to the student via the University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;A placement fee of £500 will be paid to NHS employers, once students have been confirmed as starting on course by the university. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Return to Nursing Practice course is a combination of classroom and clinical placement based learning.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bournemouth University are planning a course to commence in January 2020. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; University of Southampton is not currently running a course.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The return to practice course is a combination of classroom and placement based learning which takes between 3 and 6 months to complete. Throughout the course the learner will develop a portfolio, of skills, which will be sent to the Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) to record the completion of their RtNP course and re-registration. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The course will take approximately three months to complete, although some may take longer dependent on clinical placement hours required, length of time out of practice and length of time previously in practice. During this time the learners will be expected to complete a minimum of 150 clinical hours. They will be allocated to an Assessor whilst on placement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Through the duration of the RtNP course the nurses are employed within Southern Health on an honorary contract and although we cannot guarantee a post on completion there are usually plenty of employment opportunities available. For more information about Job Opportunities please contact the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Recruitment Department&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What are the next steps?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in a returning to nursing practice position, you can apply via the NHS Jobs website.  We will be advertising to recruit to the Bournemouth University course which starts in March 2021 and our advert will be out in October 2020. Interviews will be held in January 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you have applied for a RtNP place, if you are successfully shortlisted, you will be invited for an interview. If you are offered a place on the RtNP course, we will then consider appropriate placement opportunities. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like more information please contact the Learning Environment Team, who will be happy to help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: &lt;strong&gt;Friday 11th December&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date: &lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tuesday 19th January 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
